A fuzz target is a function that LibFuzzer uses to test your code. The signature of the fuzz target is:
```cpp
extern "C" int LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput(const uint8_t *data, size_t size);
```

In this function:
- `data`: The fuzzed input.
- `size`: The size of the fuzzed input.

Example:
```cpp
#include <string>
extern "C" int LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput(const uint8_t *data, size_t size) {
    std::string input(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(data), size);
    if (input == "crash") {
        abort();
    }
    return 0;
}
```

`LLVMFuzzerInitialize` is an optional function that runs before any fuzzing begins. It can be used for one-time setup tasks:

```cpp
extern "C" int LLVMFuzzerInitialize(int *argc, char ***argv) {
    // Initialize resources here.
    return 0;
}
```
